cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with 3D shape properties and point clouds, which are common topics in computer vision research. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is also a likely category as the paper discusses shape reconstruction and uses well-structured triangle meshes. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper proposes a deep-learning based approach for estimating local shape properties. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper uses machine learning techniques to extract information from point clouds. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible category as the paper proposes a neural network architecture for learning local shape properties.
